Some shows aren't that bad.

Steven Universe and Amazing World of Gumball are still watchable.

It's Adult Swim that has REALLY hit the bottom of the barrel.
http://i.imgur.com/DjORHu5.gifv

Oh, don't get me wrong, some shows on Adult Swim are still perfectly fine and are more than watchable. But aside from Rick and Morty, there's nothing really NEW that belongs there.

Decker is a prime example of what does not belong on Adult Swim.
Mike Tyson Mysteries.

Instead of hellbenders, we got mr.pickles. 

Why has god forsaken us :(

I agree that most shows on Adult Swim are ass. I am more than willing to watch Robot Chicken when they play that and of course Rick&Morty is a masterpiece, but apart from pretty much those two, I kind of despise everything.

At least Family Guy, American Dad, Bob's Burgers and The Cleaveland Show are 100% cartoons.

Might be all reruns but they are more than qualified for Adult Swim.

Okay, I forgot about Bob's Burgers; that is a show my whole family watches together, but we stream it, so I guess I just didn't realize it was Adult Swim. I also agree the other three MacFarlanes have some very amusing moments, they just aren't shows I would prioritize. In general, I don't enjoy any of the live action shows on adult swim, and have always found King of the Hill boring (though I think a good sized group of people like it). Something I would add is that adult swim may have a high variance between good and bad shows, but their ad breaks are much more enjoyable than most TV Networks.
Honestly the Tim and Eric series and similar shows were terrible to me. Incredibly hit or miss humor mixed with the lowest of toilet humor.

Dear god, that show was so absolutely terrible that there was literally NOTHING that redeemed it as a show.

AND IT'S STILL SHOVED ONTO ADULT SWIM WITH NOTHING MORE THAN MINIMAL CGI EFFECTS AS ITS CARTOON MATERIAL!!!

Cartoonish antics are not enough. If you're gonna have cartoonish antics, need to be over the top to the point where they REQUIRE CGI.

To that end, "Your Pretty Face is going to Hell" hits the borderline for the qualification of being a cartoon on Cartoon Network.

Shows like Decker, Tim and Eric, and the cat puppet bullshit do not qualify as cartoons (nor are cartoonish enough, whereas "Who Framed Roger Rabbit" would be).
